# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CrewHaus Shape UIs — environment & secrets
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (same folder) and fill in real values.
# `.env` is gitignored; only this `.example` template is committed.
#
# WHERE SECRETS CAN LIVE (loaded by the host, in increasing precedence):
#   1. ./.env                    repo root — applied to EVERY shape. Best place
#                                for a provider key you reuse across shapes.
#   2. <shape>/.env              per-shape override.
#   3. <shape>/harness/.env      next to your compiled bundle (highest).
#   • cf-worker shapes use <shape>/harness/.dev.vars instead (Cloudflare's
#     native local-secrets format) — see that shape's .dev.vars.example.
# An exported shell variable always overrides any .env file.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Provider credential — which one you need depends on `agent.model` in your spec.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxx
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxx
# GEMINI_API_KEY=xxxxxxxx
# Local / OpenAI-compatible servers and the full provider matrix are documented
# in factory/.env.example and packages/model-router/README.md.

# ── Host / runtime knobs (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# CREWHAUS_UI_PORT=4100        # port the UI server listens on (default 4100)
# CREWHAUS_SANDBOX=docker      # set to `noop` to disable the code-exec sandbox floor

# Anything your spec references with ${VAR} (tool configs, MCP servers, channel
# tokens, chain RPC URLs, wallet keys, …) also goes here. See each shape's
# harness/.env.example for shape-specific hints.
